  <data key="d17">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d18">such is the multitude of a home or family , and this is ruled by "domestic prudence ": and such again is the multitude of a city or kingdom, the ruling principle of which is "regnative prudence " in the ruler, and "political prudence ," simply so called, in the subjects | And therefore, just as prudence commonly so called which governs the individual , is distinct from political prudence , so must domestic prudence be distinct from both.</data>
  <data key="d19">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
  <data key="d20">subjective</data>
</edge>
