<edge source="concept.euboulia" target="st.ii-ii.q051.a001" id="edge.concept.euboulia.treated_in.st.ii-ii.q051.a001">
  <data key="d7">edge.concept.euboulia.treated_in.st.ii-ii.q051.a001</data>
  <data key="d8">concept.euboulia</data>
  <data key="d9">Euboulia</data>
  <data key="d10">prudence_part</data>
  <data key="d11">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d12">st.ii-ii.q051.a001</data>
  <data key="d13">II-II q.51 a.1 — Is euboulia a virtue?</data>
  <data key="d14">article</data>
  <data key="d15">ann.st-ii-ii-q051-a001-resp-concept-euboulia-treated-in-st-ii-ii-q051-a001</data>
  <data key="d16">st.ii-ii.q051.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d17">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d18">But euboulia (deliberating well) signifies goodness of counsel, for it is derived from the eu , good , and boule , counsel, being "a good counsel" or rather "a disposition to take good counsel." Hence it is evident that euboulia (deliberating well) is a human virtue .</data>
  <data key="d19">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
  <data key="d20"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="concept.euboulia" target="st.ii-ii.q051.a002" id="edge.concept.euboulia.treated_in.st.ii-ii.q051.a002">
  <data key="d7">edge.concept.euboulia.treated_in.st.ii-ii.q051.a002</data>
  <data key="d8">concept.euboulia</data>
  <data key="d9">Euboulia</data>
  <data key="d10">prudence_part</data>
  <data key="d11">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d12">st.ii-ii.q051.a002</data>
  <data key="d13">II-II q.51 a.2 — Is it a special virtue, distinct from prudence?</data>
  <data key="d14">article</data>
  <data key="d15">ann.st-ii-ii-q051-a002-resp-concept-euboulia-treated-in-st-ii-ii-q051-a002</data>
  <data key="d16">st.ii-ii.q051.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d17">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d18">Consequently euboulia (deliberating well) which makes man take good counsel must needs be a distinct virtue from prudence , which makes man command well</data>
  <data key="d19">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
  <data key="d20"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="concept.false_prudence" target="st.ii-ii.q047.a013" id="edge.concept.false_prudence.treated_in.st.ii-ii.q047.a013">
