  <data key="d17">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d18">thus an army is gathered together to fight, and the prudence that governs this is called "military." There is also the multitude that is united together for the whole of life | Therefore in those things also which are in accordance with reason, there should be not only "political" prudence , which disposes in a suitable manner such things as belong to the common good , but also a "military" prudence , whereby hostile attacks are repelled.</data>
