  <data key="d15">ann.st-ii-ii-q048-a001-resp-concept-political-prudence-subjective-part-of-concept-prudence | ann.st-ii-ii-q050-a002-resp-concept-political-prudence-subjective-part-of-concept-prudence</data>
  <data key="d16">st.ii-ii.q048.a001.resp | st.ii-ii.q050.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d17">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d18">such is the multitude of a home or family , and this is ruled by "domestic prudence ": and such again is the multitude of a city or kingdom, the ruling principle of which is "regnative prudence " in the ruler, and "political prudence ," simply so called, in the subjects | and to this belongs that species of prudence which is called political.</data>
