  <data key="d16">st.ii-ii.q049.a004.resp</data>
  <data key="d17">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d18">Now just as docility consists in a man being well disposed to acquire a right opinion from another man , so shrewdness is an apt disposition to acquire a right estimate by oneself, yet so that shrewdness be taken for eustochia , of which it is a part</data>
  <data key="d19">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
  <data key="d20"></data>
</edge>
