  <data key="d13">Prudence</data>
  <data key="d14">virtue</data>
  <data key="d15">ann.st-ii-ii-q048-a001-resp-concept-synesis-potential-part-of-concept-prudence</data>
  <data key="d16">st.ii-ii.q048.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d17">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d18">On this way the parts of prudence are " good counsel," which concerns counsel, "synesis," which concerns judgment in matters of ordinary occurrence, and "gnome," which concerns judgment in matters of exception to the law : while " prudence " is about the chief act, viz</data>
  <data key="d19">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
